# ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
# ║  ShadowGuard WAF — .gitignore                               ║
# ║                                                              ║
# ║  SECURITY NOTE:                                              ║
# ║  This WAF protects applications. Publishing detection        ║
# ║  logic, trained weights, and feature extraction details      ║
# ║  would allow adversaries to craft bypass payloads.           ║
# ║  Files listed here are kept private deliberately.            ║
# ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CORE WAF ENGINE  — DO NOT PUBLISH (bypass risk)
# These files contain detection logic. Exposing them allows
# an attacker to craft inputs that score 0 on every rule.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# The main application — contains all regex rules, soft score
# thresholds, ML invocation gates, and threat DB.
# Share only architecture diagrams and high-level descriptions.
app.py

# Target application — intentionally vulnerable app used for
# testing. Never expose this on a public repo (it's literally
# full of injection holes).
target_app.py


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# TRAINED MODEL ARTIFACTS  — DO NOT PUBLISH
# Publishing the .pkl exposes:
#   - Feature importance rankings (what the model watches for)
#   - Decision boundaries (what scores stay below threshold)
#   - Weight vectors (adversarial example generation)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
models/
!models/.gitkeep


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# DATASETS  — DO NOT PUBLISH (licensing + size)
# CSIC 2010 has academic license restrictions.
# Raw traffic logs may contain PII.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
data/
!data/.gitkeep


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# RUNTIME LOGS  — DO NOT PUBLISH
# Logs contain real IP addresses, actual attack payloads,
# timing information, and potentially sensitive request data.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
logs/
!logs/.gitkeep
*.log
*.ndjson


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ENVIRONMENT & SECRETS
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*.pem
*.crt
*.p12
secrets/
config/local.py
config/production.py


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PYTHON
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
venv/
.venv/
env/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
*.egg
*.egg-info/
dist/
build/
.eggs/
pip-wheel-metadata/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# JUPYTER (if used for model exploration)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*.ipynb


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OS FILES
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# IDE
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.project
.classpath


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# DOCKER VOLUMES / TEMP
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
.docker/
docker-volumes/
*.tar
*.gz
tmp/
temp/


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# WHAT IS INTENTIONALLY PUBLIC  (override above with !)
# These files demonstrate skill without enabling bypasses:
#   README.md         — Architecture, setup, metrics
#   GUIDE.md          — LAN testing walkthrough
#   Dockerfile        — Container hardening approach
#   docker-compose.yml— Production stack design
#   nginx/nginx.conf  — Reverse proxy configuration
#   requirements.txt  — Technology choices
#   01_prepare_dataset.py — Feature engineering methodology
#   02_train_model.py     — Training pipeline (not detection logic)
#   lan_attack_test.py    — Testing framework
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
!README.md
!GUIDE.md
!Dockerfile
!docker-compose.yml
!nginx/
!requirements.txt
!01_prepare_dataset.py
!02_train_model.py
!lan_attack_test.py
!.env.example
!models/.gitkeep
!data/.gitkeep
!logs/.gitkeep